snippet.title: Pre-Calculus - How to find the slant asymptote of a rational function
snippet.description: This example shows how to find the slant asymptote for a rational function.  Remember that a rational function will only have a slant asymptote if the top polynomial Is one degree larger than the bottom polynomial.  For more videos please visit http://www.mysecretmathtutor.com
